DLL: Dynamic Link Library 
Usage:  When a program is launched, links to the necessary .dll files which are created.
If a static link is created, the .dll files will be in use if the program is active. 
If a dynamic link is created, the .dll files will only be used when needed. 

Usage of DLL for current Project:

•	Checks the internet connection.
•	Gets the current or new location from the database and updates the same to UI.
•	Checks the water level.
•	Flood level is calculated and gives updates to the UI.
•	Duration is measured and updated to UI.
  For any on click function in the UI layer, dlls helps to link to db to retrieve the information and then the businesslayer
  again reverts the results back to the UI 
